WEBVTT

00:02.669 --> 00:04.470
Heads up--there's
our perp, looking all

00:04.471 --> 00:07.339
Perpy, just perping
his way down perp street.

00:07.341 --> 00:08.741
- Take a picture!
- Give me one second.

00:08.743 --> 00:11.043
This light is really
unflattering for his complexion.

00:11.045 --> 00:12.211
It doesn't have
to be perfect.

00:12.213 --> 00:15.381
He's held up four electronic
stores at gunpoint.

00:15.383 --> 00:17.249
Man, I wish you hadn't read
that annie leibovitz book.

00:17.251 --> 00:19.184
Quit calling it a book.
It was a visual journey.

00:19.186 --> 00:20.486
You probably think I should
shoot this in color

00:20.488 --> 00:21.520
Instead of black and white.

00:21.522 --> 00:24.223
Why have you been shooting
black and white?

00:24.225 --> 00:25.791
Wait.
Where's he going now?

00:25.793 --> 00:27.226
Come on.

00:27.228 --> 00:31.096
[casual music]

00:31.098 --> 00:33.665
Damn it.
Nypd! Freeze!

00:33.667 --> 00:36.668
[hard rock music]

00:36.670 --> 00:38.137
♪ ♪

00:38.139 --> 00:39.338
He's trapped!

00:39.340 --> 00:40.472
(jake)
top-of-car foot chase!

00:40.474 --> 00:42.741
My birthday wish
finally came true!

00:42.743 --> 00:48.147
♪ ♪

00:48.149 --> 00:49.348
Keep it up, jake!
He's yours!

00:49.350 --> 00:50.349
He's yours!
He's yours!

00:50.351 --> 00:53.519
I feel like the coolest person
in new york city!

00:53.521 --> 00:54.753
[screams]

00:54.755 --> 00:57.756
[upbeat music]

00:57.758 --> 01:06.065
♪ ♪

01:14.774 --> 01:17.743
[chill music]

01:17.745 --> 01:19.578
Ooh, nice pimp walk,
pimp.

01:19.580 --> 01:21.213
Well, thank you,
pimpin' playa.

01:21.215 --> 01:23.215
Whoa.
That is not a pimp walk.

01:23.217 --> 01:24.383
That's a limp walk.

01:24.385 --> 01:26.085
You sure you should
be here today, jake?

01:26.087 --> 01:27.319
I mean, you
wiped out hard.

01:27.321 --> 01:28.620
It wasn't so much
a wipeout

01:28.622 --> 01:30.489
As it was a controlled
power fall, sarge.

01:30.491 --> 01:32.458
Well...

01:32.460 --> 01:33.859
That's his
disagreement squeak.

01:33.861 --> 01:35.761
You wiped out.
What'd the doctor say?

01:35.763 --> 01:37.663
Welcome; we haven't
seen you in 11 years.

01:37.665 --> 01:39.531
Haven't been to the
doctor in 11 years.

01:39.533 --> 01:41.133
How trill is that?

01:41.135 --> 01:42.134
Your tone's braggy,

01:42.136 --> 01:43.268
But your words
are real sad.

01:43.270 --> 01:44.236
Hmm.

01:44.238 --> 01:45.504
Did he clear you
for active duty?

01:45.506 --> 01:46.872
First of all, the
doctor was a woman.

01:46.874 --> 01:49.641
There's a such thing
as women doctors, sarge.

01:49.643 --> 01:51.310
I lied for effect.
It was a man.

01:51.312 --> 01:53.178
And he said that I
was perfectly fine,

01:53.180 --> 01:54.480
Except for three
cracked ribs

01:54.482 --> 01:55.881
And a broken toe,
which were right next

01:55.883 --> 01:56.882
To two other broken toes.

01:56.884 --> 01:58.183
Did he clear you or not?

01:58.185 --> 01:59.451
[laughing]
he did not. All right.

01:59.453 --> 02:01.353
Let's get to work, guys.
We got a perp to catch.

02:01.355 --> 02:03.322
Oh, forget that.
Uh-uh. No. Look.

02:03.324 --> 02:05.424
There's a apb out
for your guy.

02:05.426 --> 02:06.725
Lots of cops
are looking for him.

02:06.727 --> 02:08.160
You don't need
to be here.

02:08.162 --> 02:09.728
Sarge, I know this case
better than anyone,

02:09.729 --> 02:11.697
And I am this close
to solving it.

02:11.699 --> 02:12.698
[inhales sharply]

02:12.700 --> 02:14.433
Your fingers are
really far apart.

02:14.435 --> 02:16.502
Yeah, I also have a hairline
fracture in my thumb.

02:16.504 --> 02:19.771
Mankind's least important
finger--am I right?

02:19.773 --> 02:21.907
Please.
Please, please, please.

02:21.909 --> 02:23.342
Just let me stay
on the case, all right?

02:23.344 --> 02:24.610
I promise I won't go
into the field

02:24.612 --> 02:26.211
Or do anything dangerous.

02:26.213 --> 02:28.647
You can work the case
from right here,

02:28.649 --> 02:30.349
But you are tied
to your desk.

02:30.351 --> 02:32.184
Ooh.
Tied to my desk.

02:32.186 --> 02:34.319
Mr. Grey will see
you now, sarge.

02:35.321 --> 02:36.688
You wanted to see me, sir?

02:37.891 --> 02:39.591
We have a situation,
and it's bad.

02:39.593 --> 02:40.659
Check your e-mail.

02:43.329 --> 02:44.463
- No.
- Yes.

02:44.465 --> 02:46.265
Kevin insists
on you and marcus

02:46.267 --> 02:47.599
Joining us for dinner
at our house.

02:47.601 --> 02:48.867
But we agreed to keep
our personal

02:48.869 --> 02:50.369
And professional
lives separate.

02:50.371 --> 02:52.204
It is weird enough
I am dating your nephew

02:52.206 --> 02:54.239
Without dragging your
husband and dog into it.

02:54.241 --> 02:55.240
You think I want this?

02:55.242 --> 02:56.909
Because I do not want this.

02:56.911 --> 03:00.279
Sadly, marcus and kevin
can be held off no longer.

03:00.281 --> 03:01.713
Okay.

03:01.715 --> 03:02.915
So what's
our play here?

03:02.917 --> 03:04.183
My stomach's
a little off.

03:04.185 --> 03:06.818
Well, I've used the sick
excuse for you eight times.

03:06.820 --> 03:07.786
I think they're
catching on.

03:07.788 --> 03:10.355
No one would ever
believe that.

03:10.357 --> 03:11.890
No.
This is happening.

03:11.892 --> 03:15.727
I have a plan to keep things
from getting too personal.

03:15.729 --> 03:18.530
I'm inviting some
intimacy buffers.

03:18.532 --> 03:20.632
Dinner party at your house?

03:20.634 --> 03:22.701
Oh, mama!

03:22.703 --> 03:23.936
(gina)
I will be there.

03:23.938 --> 03:25.704
All I ask is that you
clear the furniture

03:25.706 --> 03:29.641
So I can show kev
some of my new dance opera.

03:29.643 --> 03:30.642
Why just some of it?

03:30.644 --> 03:33.212
Yes; nothing would
make me happier.

03:33.214 --> 03:34.913
See you Thursday
at 8:00.

03:34.915 --> 03:37.416
Copy that, cap-I-tan!

03:37.418 --> 03:38.717
Later, skater.

03:38.719 --> 03:40.219
[laughs]

03:40.221 --> 03:41.220
Yes.

03:41.222 --> 03:42.788
This is wonderful.

03:42.790 --> 03:43.956
The dinner's not
for four days,

03:43.958 --> 03:45.424
And you're already
freaking out.

03:45.426 --> 03:49.328
Did you not just hear me
say, "later, skater"?

03:50.231 --> 03:52.931
There's a slight chance
that, in the past,

03:52.933 --> 03:55.000
I may have tried a little
too hard around the captain.

03:55.002 --> 03:57.903
So this time, I'm gonna
be super chill.

03:57.905 --> 03:58.971
Good plan.

03:58.973 --> 04:00.839
Whoa!

04:00.841 --> 04:02.808
It just says
you got uninvited.

04:02.810 --> 04:03.809
What?

04:03.811 --> 04:04.843
Oh, honey.

04:04.845 --> 04:06.845
Oh. I get it.

04:06.847 --> 04:08.647
You're joking.

04:08.649 --> 04:09.815
See? I'm cool.

04:09.817 --> 04:11.717
I get jokes.

04:11.719 --> 04:12.985
Boyle, have you
seen jake?

04:12.987 --> 04:15.854
I was out getting him
some healing broth.

04:15.856 --> 04:17.656
I was torn between
chicken or beef,

04:17.658 --> 04:18.690
But then it hit me.

04:18.692 --> 04:19.891
Goat!

04:19.892 --> 04:22.561
[crashing]

04:26.799 --> 04:28.300
What happened?
I heard a bang!

04:28.302 --> 04:29.868
No. No bang.
Everything's totally normal.

04:29.870 --> 04:33.038
It looks, to me, like
you did something stupid

04:33.040 --> 04:35.307
Like try to lift
a heavy box.

04:35.309 --> 04:37.042
Sarge, come on.
In my condition?

04:37.044 --> 04:39.044
Suck it, macgyver.

04:39.046 --> 04:40.646
[grunts]

04:40.648 --> 04:42.581
[crashing]

04:42.583 --> 04:43.782
Pretty elegant
solution, right?

04:43.784 --> 04:44.783
No!

04:44.785 --> 04:46.485
Everything
fell everywhere.

04:46.487 --> 04:48.787
All you had to do
was sit at your desk.

04:48.789 --> 04:49.888
What is your problem?

04:49.890 --> 04:51.056
I don't have a problem.

04:51.058 --> 04:52.557
I'm just trying
to solve this case,

04:52.559 --> 04:53.959
And everyone's
making a huge deal

04:53.961 --> 04:55.527
Because I have
a few minor injuries

04:55.529 --> 04:58.397
To my ribs, ankle,
hand, toes, and jaw.

04:58.399 --> 04:59.665
- Jaw?
- Yeah, that just happened.

04:59.667 --> 05:00.966
I got hit in the face
with a box.

05:00.968 --> 05:02.334
But look.
I'm fine.

05:02.336 --> 05:03.935
- I promise you.
- No, you're not.

05:03.937 --> 05:05.671
I'm done with this,
peralta.

05:05.673 --> 05:07.039
Go home and get better.

05:07.041 --> 05:08.040
Now!

05:08.042 --> 05:10.642
But I'm taking this box
of evidence with me.

05:10.644 --> 05:12.077
If you can pick it up,
you can take it.

05:12.079 --> 05:13.345
Deal.

05:15.615 --> 05:18.684
[groaning]

05:20.386 --> 05:23.455
[groaning continues]

05:25.425 --> 05:26.591
[breathing heavily]

05:26.593 --> 05:29.094
See? I'm fine.

05:30.330 --> 05:31.330
Miss me, miss me,

05:31.332 --> 05:32.431
Now you got to kiss me!

05:32.433 --> 05:33.532
I'm talking to you.

05:33.534 --> 05:35.033
Jake, what are you doing here?

05:35.035 --> 05:38.070
You're supposed to take
a full week off of work.

05:38.072 --> 05:39.338
Come on, sarge.

05:39.340 --> 05:40.339
Does it look like
I'm on the job?

05:40.341 --> 05:41.406
Okay then.

05:41.408 --> 05:43.809
Taking your advice
to rest and relax

05:43.811 --> 05:46.011
Swinging by
to pick up charles,

05:46.013 --> 05:47.713
And then we're headed
to sunny, beachy,

05:47.715 --> 05:49.681
Only recently devastated
by a financial crisis

05:49.683 --> 05:50.782
Atlantic cit-ay!

05:50.784 --> 05:53.952
Jake and I are going on
the coolest vacation ever.

05:53.954 --> 05:55.520
Official trip nickname:

05:55.522 --> 05:56.655
Ac/dc.

05:56.657 --> 05:57.823
Atlantic city
dudes club.

05:57.825 --> 05:58.924
Yeah.
That's gonna change.

05:58.926 --> 05:59.958
But check it out, sarge.

05:59.960 --> 06:01.126
Boyle and I
are staying at...

06:01.128 --> 06:03.028
(both)
♪ the ravenna ♪

06:03.030 --> 06:04.963
Damn.

06:04.965 --> 06:08.567
Yeah, I've been trying to get
jake down there forever.

06:08.569 --> 06:10.635
Had I known all it'd
take was a few broken bones,

06:10.637 --> 06:12.537
I would've hit him with
a baseball bat years ago!

06:12.539 --> 06:13.605
Mm-mm.

06:13.607 --> 06:15.474
Sarge, it's a spa
and a casino.

06:15.476 --> 06:16.675
A spasino!

06:16.677 --> 06:17.976
(jake)
one of the room service options

06:17.978 --> 06:19.378
Is a carving station.

06:19.380 --> 06:21.680
♪ talking prime rib in bed ♪

06:21.682 --> 06:22.948
(jake)
and what's this?

06:22.950 --> 06:24.883
I'm using a blanket
as a napkin.

06:24.885 --> 06:26.618
That's fancy.
That's fancy.

06:26.620 --> 06:27.619
Real fancy.

06:27.621 --> 06:28.620
All right.

06:28.622 --> 06:29.788
Well, that sounds
good, jake.

06:29.790 --> 06:31.423
Sounds like you guys
are gonna have fun.

06:31.425 --> 06:33.458
Oh--oh, we will
'cause we're staying at...

06:33.460 --> 06:35.560
(both)
♪ the ravenna ♪

06:35.562 --> 06:37.896
Jake, this is not
the ravenna.

06:37.898 --> 06:41.066
No, it is not, but it
is the world-famous

06:41.068 --> 06:42.868
Seafam motel!

06:42.870 --> 06:44.436
I think the "o"
fell off.

06:44.438 --> 06:47.539
The ravenna had
a four-star restaurant.

06:47.541 --> 06:49.908
This place has a weird
amount of dead seagulls,

06:49.910 --> 06:50.909
Even for ac.

06:50.911 --> 06:52.644
All right. Fine.

06:52.646 --> 06:53.945
It's not a vacation.

06:53.947 --> 06:56.882
My perp has a brother
who lives in this dump,

06:56.884 --> 06:58.583
And I think he's hiding out
with him here.

06:58.585 --> 06:59.684
Seriously?

06:59.686 --> 07:01.153
I was looking forward
to this trip.

07:01.155 --> 07:02.687
I can't believe
you lied to me.

07:02.689 --> 07:04.423
It wasn't a lie.

07:04.425 --> 07:05.424
It was...

07:05.426 --> 07:08.427
An illusion!

07:08.429 --> 07:09.995
All right. It was a lie.
I'm sorry.

07:09.997 --> 07:11.430
I had to make it
sound really cool

07:11.432 --> 07:12.964
So you'd drop everything
and come with me.

07:12.966 --> 07:15.133
I can't let olson walk,
and I can't catch him alone.

07:15.135 --> 07:17.002
Plus, this is gonna
be super fun!

07:17.004 --> 07:18.737
New trip nickname:
Ac/dc.

07:18.739 --> 07:20.972
Atlantic city
detectives club.

07:20.974 --> 07:23.074
Oh... Okay! Fine!

07:23.076 --> 07:25.043
You know I can't say no
to a good trip nickname.

07:25.045 --> 07:26.812
There he is.
Ugh! Arm! Rib!

07:26.814 --> 07:28.113
Arm! Rib! Shoulder?

07:28.115 --> 07:29.548
Ooh.

07:29.550 --> 07:31.516
Marcus. Detective diaz.
What a surprise.

07:31.518 --> 07:33.151
I didn't expect you
for another 9 1/2 minutes.

07:33.153 --> 07:34.152
See?

07:34.154 --> 07:35.854
Told you it was rude
to be early.

07:35.856 --> 07:38.223
Well, let's cancel the entire
evening and try again next year.

07:38.225 --> 07:39.224
[laughing]
hey.

07:39.226 --> 07:40.659
She is hilarious.

07:40.661 --> 07:42.494
I thought you might need
some help setting up.

07:42.496 --> 07:43.829
Oh, I'll put these
in some water.

07:43.831 --> 07:46.998
Marcus, you can help
with the boeuf bourguignon.

07:47.000 --> 07:48.934
I subbed shallots
for onions in the mirepoix.

07:48.936 --> 07:51.236
No!
Are you kidding?

07:51.238 --> 07:53.672
I have no idea
what he's talking about.

07:55.575 --> 07:56.808
I'm sorry.
We're screwed.

07:56.810 --> 07:57.976
I should just
break up with him.

07:57.978 --> 08:00.612
No, no, no, no.
Santiago is always on time.

08:00.614 --> 08:02.080
We only have to make
small talk for...

08:02.082 --> 08:03.882
8 minutes
and 45 seconds.

08:03.884 --> 08:08.553
Acceptable topics include
what constitutes a grain,

08:08.555 --> 08:09.754
The hubble
space telescope,

08:09.756 --> 08:11.022
Orchid varietals,

08:11.024 --> 08:12.724
The birth
of the transistor...

08:12.726 --> 08:13.892
We only have to fill
8 minutes.

08:13.894 --> 08:16.995
Sure, but think
about it as 480 seconds,

08:16.997 --> 08:18.530
And you'll see
why I'm concerned.

08:18.532 --> 08:19.931
Oh, my god.

08:19.933 --> 08:21.233
Uh-oh, amy.

08:21.235 --> 08:23.568
Train's moving
real slow.

08:23.570 --> 08:25.570
We're gonna
be epically late.

08:25.572 --> 08:27.806
Keep your reaction
short and to the point.

08:27.808 --> 08:28.974
I'm running out of mem.

08:28.976 --> 08:29.975
Sorry, gina.

08:29.977 --> 08:31.076
I hope we're late.

08:31.078 --> 08:32.844
That's how the
fashionable crowd lives.

08:32.846 --> 08:35.679
I told you--tonight,
I'm gonna have fun.

08:35.682 --> 08:36.748
What?

08:36.750 --> 08:38.149
I'm being chill.

08:38.150 --> 08:39.683
Why are you looking
at me like that?

08:39.686 --> 08:41.653
Because
something stinks,

08:41.655 --> 08:43.788
And it's definitely
the food you brought.

08:43.789 --> 08:45.790
I think it smells great.

08:45.792 --> 08:47.826
It's my mom's famous
nicoise salad.

08:47.828 --> 08:49.895
Amy, all your
cooking stinks.

08:49.897 --> 08:51.129
Why would you
even get involved

08:51.131 --> 08:52.230
With tuna and egg?

08:52.232 --> 08:53.965
No one else seems
to mind it.

08:53.967 --> 08:55.000
We mind!

08:55.002 --> 08:56.601
We really,
really mind.

08:56.603 --> 08:57.702
Just throw it out.

08:57.704 --> 08:59.170
I will not
throw it out,

08:59.172 --> 09:00.972
But I will
open a window

09:00.974 --> 09:02.974
Because I'm a nice person.

09:05.578 --> 09:07.579
And I'm an even
nicer person!

09:07.581 --> 09:08.580
Bye-bye, salad!

09:08.582 --> 09:10.549
No!

09:10.551 --> 09:13.552
[suspenseful music]

09:13.554 --> 09:16.121
Yo!
Still no movement.

09:16.123 --> 09:17.222
How was the
snack machine?

09:17.224 --> 09:19.224
Ah. Snacks abound!

09:19.226 --> 09:20.759
Told you this place
was awesome.

09:20.761 --> 09:22.761
My theory is that
olson and his brother

09:22.763 --> 09:23.962
Have been using it
as a home base

09:23.964 --> 09:25.830
While they rob places
up and down the coast.

09:25.832 --> 09:27.899
Fascinating.
Fascinating.

09:27.901 --> 09:29.734
Do you desire
a crispened potato?

09:29.736 --> 09:31.570
Ah, don't mind
if I dooble.

09:31.572 --> 09:33.038
Wait a minute.
"crispened potato."

09:33.040 --> 09:34.139
Why are you
fancy-talking?

09:34.141 --> 09:35.574
How dare you, sir?

09:35.576 --> 09:37.042
I speak the common tongue.

09:37.044 --> 09:38.043
There it is again.

09:38.045 --> 09:39.311
You only do that
when you're lying

09:39.313 --> 09:40.312
Or hiding something.

09:40.314 --> 09:41.580
Hiding? Ha!

09:41.582 --> 09:42.581
Pish-posh!

09:42.583 --> 09:43.582
[loud knocking]

09:43.584 --> 09:44.749
(terry)
housekeeping!

09:44.751 --> 09:46.585
That's not housekeeping!
That's betrayal!

09:46.587 --> 09:48.320
I can't believe
you called the sarge!

09:49.722 --> 09:51.590
Hey, sarge.

09:51.592 --> 09:53.592
Don't "hey, sarge,"
me, peralta!

09:53.594 --> 09:55.760
I'm about to break the rest
of your damn body!

09:55.762 --> 09:56.895
Okay. Fine.

09:56.897 --> 09:57.996
I accept my fate.

09:57.998 --> 09:59.731
Just take a picture
of my penis first,

09:59.733 --> 10:01.333
For posterity, and then
do what you must.

10:02.735 --> 10:04.803
Amy says that we should
start dinner without her.

10:04.805 --> 10:06.705
Then she writes,
"whatevs," colon,

10:06.707 --> 10:08.840
Hyphen, closed parenthesis.

10:08.842 --> 10:11.343
It's much nicer
just the four of us.

10:11.345 --> 10:12.911
I mean, we can
really get into it.

10:12.913 --> 10:14.913
Yeah, let's do
just that.

10:14.915 --> 10:17.716
So marcus, what
orchids can you name?

10:17.718 --> 10:18.783
Oh, that's easy.

10:18.785 --> 10:21.853
Uh, well, here are the
orchids that I can name.

10:21.855 --> 10:24.289
<i>Beclardia, beloglottis,</i>
<i>benthamia, diphylax,</i>

10:24.291 --> 10:25.724
<i>Dipodium, evotella--</i>

10:25.726 --> 10:27.726
Raymond, you know
how much I love

10:27.728 --> 10:29.127
Hearing you talk
about orchids...

10:29.129 --> 10:30.829
Great.
Then there's <i> eriaxis--</i>

10:30.831 --> 10:33.965
But I would love to hear
more about our guest.

10:33.967 --> 10:36.267
Rosa, tell us
about your family.

10:38.804 --> 10:39.904
I have one.

10:39.906 --> 10:42.707
You got to give him
more deets than that.

10:42.709 --> 10:44.009
Her father's a teacher.

10:44.011 --> 10:45.143
They're from
bensonhurst.

10:45.145 --> 10:46.711
Speaking of which,
have they finished

10:46.713 --> 10:48.179
Repairing the hubble
space telescope?

10:48.181 --> 10:49.247
Yes.
Six years ago.

10:49.249 --> 10:52.083
So do you have
siblings?

10:53.152 --> 10:57.255
I have...

10:57.257 --> 10:58.356
Two sisters.

11:01.060 --> 11:03.061
I have to leave this.

11:04.697 --> 11:06.064
[clears throat]

11:08.267 --> 11:09.701
Phew! Great idea.

11:09.703 --> 11:10.702
Take a breather.

11:10.704 --> 11:12.671
That was way
too personal.

11:12.673 --> 11:14.139
No one needs to know
you have sisters.

11:14.141 --> 11:15.407
New topic:

11:15.409 --> 11:17.208
The moons of jupiter.

11:18.210 --> 11:19.411
I think I might
be pregnant.

11:21.180 --> 11:22.347
Oh.

11:24.116 --> 11:27.152
Oh...

11:27.154 --> 11:29.954
Oh, n--

11:29.956 --> 11:31.423
No.

11:31.425 --> 11:33.358
I came down here
to stop you

11:33.360 --> 11:34.926
From doing
something stupid.

11:34.928 --> 11:36.995
I called the acpd
and told them

11:36.997 --> 11:39.130
We had a possible perp
at this motel.

11:39.132 --> 11:40.365
They're sending
a squad car.

11:40.367 --> 11:41.966
Wow, boyle.

11:41.968 --> 11:43.702
The fact that you
would sell me out

11:43.704 --> 11:46.137
After I brought you
to atlantic city

11:46.139 --> 11:48.473
On a half-expenses-paid,
best-friend trip.

11:48.475 --> 11:50.275
I know. I'm sorry.

11:50.277 --> 11:52.711
It's just--I was worried
about you getting hurt.

11:52.713 --> 11:54.846
No, charles!
Don't apologize!

11:54.848 --> 11:59.350
I had to miss family dinner
to drive my ass out here.

11:59.352 --> 12:01.252
Well, no one asked
you to do that.

12:01.254 --> 12:02.387
Actually, I did.
Remember?

12:02.389 --> 12:05.123
Charles, what are you
doing, bud?

12:05.125 --> 12:06.725
I just dug you out of this.

12:06.727 --> 12:07.992
Peralta, we're going home

12:07.994 --> 12:09.260
As soon as that squad car
gets here.

12:09.262 --> 12:11.262
Until then, you sit tight.

12:11.264 --> 12:12.497
You're on time out.

12:12.499 --> 12:16.401
Fine, but first,
I have to go to the bathroom.

12:16.403 --> 12:19.237
And it will be work,
due to my injured tailbone

12:19.239 --> 12:21.740
And bruised bladder.

12:21.742 --> 12:23.141
[grunting]

12:23.143 --> 12:24.142
[inhales sharply]

12:24.144 --> 12:25.910
[sighs]

12:26.846 --> 12:27.846
[dramatic music]

12:27.848 --> 12:29.447
What the hell?

12:29.449 --> 12:31.116
Oh.

12:31.118 --> 12:32.450
Please be olson.

12:32.452 --> 12:35.019
Please be olson.
Please be olson.

12:35.021 --> 12:36.187
You're not olson.

12:36.189 --> 12:37.322
[window slams shut]

12:37.324 --> 12:38.323
♪ ♪

12:38.325 --> 12:39.424
Oh, no.

12:39.426 --> 12:41.292
♪ ♪

12:41.294 --> 12:43.428
[grunting]

12:43.430 --> 12:44.796
Uh-oh.

12:47.366 --> 12:50.769
I should be at home,
taking care of my real babies.

12:50.771 --> 12:52.103
Not some big, dumb work baby.

12:52.105 --> 12:54.005
I know you're upset, sarge,
but I think the fact

12:54.007 --> 12:55.807
That you came
all the way down here

12:55.809 --> 12:57.242
Has really taught jake
a lesson.

12:57.244 --> 12:58.243
(jake)
help!

12:58.245 --> 12:59.244
And I'm wrong.

12:59.246 --> 13:02.113
- Help! Help!
- Cover yourself, jake.

13:02.115 --> 13:05.083
It's your friend
charles boyle from work!

13:05.085 --> 13:07.919
Hey, guys.

13:09.388 --> 13:10.421
What the hell
are you doing

13:10.423 --> 13:12.090
Out there, peralta?

13:12.092 --> 13:14.793
Would you believe
that my urine stream

13:14.795 --> 13:15.994
Was so powerful that it--

13:15.996 --> 13:17.228
- No!
- Okay.

13:17.230 --> 13:19.030
I thought I saw
our perp,

13:19.032 --> 13:20.799
And I know I'm not
supposed to be working,

13:20.801 --> 13:22.267
But technically,
I wasn't working

13:22.269 --> 13:24.335
Because it
wasn't our guy.

13:24.337 --> 13:25.336
Get out of the bathroom!

13:25.338 --> 13:26.404
[whispering]
yeah.

13:26.406 --> 13:28.273
We're gonna go sit
on those gross beds

13:28.275 --> 13:29.340
And talk about the fact

13:29.342 --> 13:30.475
That you have
a real problem!

13:30.477 --> 13:31.576
Okay, I get
that you're mad,

13:31.578 --> 13:33.011
And we are definitely
gonna talk,

13:33.013 --> 13:34.279
But I still haven't,
technically,

13:34.281 --> 13:36.014
Gotten to go pee, so
if you wouldn't mind--

13:36.016 --> 13:37.015
I don't care.

13:37.017 --> 13:38.283
You have lost
the right to pee.

13:38.285 --> 13:40.084
You can fidget,
little man.

13:40.086 --> 13:41.219
[scoffs]

13:41.221 --> 13:42.554
Well, it's gonna be on you

13:42.556 --> 13:44.489
When we're all covered
in my whiz.

13:44.491 --> 13:46.157
Get your ass
out there.

13:46.159 --> 13:50.195
Are your bosoms tender?

13:50.197 --> 13:52.197
I'm gonna pretend that you
didn't just ask me that.

13:52.199 --> 13:54.299
Are your senses
heightened?

13:54.301 --> 13:55.400
I think I might
be pregnant,

13:55.402 --> 13:57.869
Not bitten by
a radioactive spider.

13:57.871 --> 13:59.003
[sighs]

13:59.005 --> 14:00.371
Kevin asked me
about my sister.

14:00.373 --> 14:01.606
She just told me
she's pregnant,

14:01.608 --> 14:03.041
And that made me think--

14:03.043 --> 14:04.442
I've been feeling
run down lately,

14:04.444 --> 14:05.910
My stomach's been weird,

14:05.912 --> 14:07.111
And I just did
the math in my head

14:07.113 --> 14:08.346
And I think I'm
a little bit late.

14:08.348 --> 14:10.081
Late to...

14:10.083 --> 14:11.216
Oh, right. Right.

14:11.218 --> 14:13.017
Your...

14:13.019 --> 14:14.018
What if I'm pregnant?

14:14.020 --> 14:14.986
Do I tell marcus?

14:14.988 --> 14:17.155
How do you take care
of those things?

14:17.157 --> 14:18.223
Why are their heads so soft?

14:18.225 --> 14:19.557
Before you spiral
any more,

14:19.559 --> 14:21.025
You should take
a pregnancy test.

14:21.027 --> 14:22.594
Yes. Smart.
Immediately.

14:22.596 --> 14:23.962
Oh.

14:23.964 --> 14:25.563
Immediately
immediately.

14:25.565 --> 14:28.433
I'll figure out a way
to get you out of here

14:28.435 --> 14:30.001
Without arousing
suspicion.

14:30.003 --> 14:33.872
Blowing through my orchid
material so quickly.

14:33.874 --> 14:36.140
Jake, you put work ahead
of everything else,

14:36.142 --> 14:40.111
Remember cagney and lacey's
third birthday party?

14:40.113 --> 14:41.913
I hired you
as jakels the clown.

14:41.915 --> 14:47.552
And jeremy the giraffe
has a very long neck!

14:47.554 --> 14:49.520
That's it.

14:49.522 --> 14:51.923
That little girl
was strangled!

14:51.925 --> 14:54.025
You were thinking that
at a kid's party.

14:54.027 --> 14:55.093
Life is more
than just

14:55.095 --> 14:56.327
Whatever case
you're working on.

14:56.329 --> 14:58.162
If you don't figure out
how to balance things,

14:58.164 --> 14:59.430
You're gonna burn out
or get hurt.

14:59.432 --> 15:00.498
Oh, look.

15:00.500 --> 15:01.499
You did get hurt.

15:01.501 --> 15:03.935
You guys make
some great points,

15:03.937 --> 15:05.670
But counterpoint:

15:05.672 --> 15:07.005
I am right all the time.

15:07.007 --> 15:08.039
There's our perp.

15:08.041 --> 15:10.608
[suspenseful music]

15:10.610 --> 15:12.277
All right. Let's go!

15:12.279 --> 15:13.278
Jake!

15:13.280 --> 15:15.146
Observe him
from a safe distance

15:15.148 --> 15:17.115
While we wait for the
atlantic city pd to show up.

15:17.117 --> 15:19.017
My exact instinct
as well, sarge.

15:19.019 --> 15:20.151
Good thinking.

15:20.153 --> 15:22.954
Are you certain we have
to cut the party short?

15:22.956 --> 15:24.322
Yes; unfortunately,
detective diaz

15:24.324 --> 15:26.424
Has an unexpected emergency
to take care of.

15:26.426 --> 15:27.425
All right.

15:27.427 --> 15:28.526
Do you need
to go as well?

15:28.528 --> 15:34.065
But still advanced enough
that detective diaz's talents

15:34.067 --> 15:37.201
Are best qualified
to handle the...

15:37.203 --> 15:38.503
Non-emergency
emergency.

15:38.505 --> 15:39.504
Yes. Precisely.

15:39.506 --> 15:40.638
See? She's great.

15:40.640 --> 15:41.639
I should go do that.

15:41.641 --> 15:42.640
Now.

15:42.642 --> 15:44.542
Yes.

15:46.178 --> 15:47.478
- Hey. What's up?
- Hi.

15:47.480 --> 15:49.380
Sorry we're so late.

15:49.382 --> 15:50.515
Actually,
the party is over.

15:50.517 --> 15:51.549
What?

15:51.551 --> 15:53.284
The party is over!

15:54.219 --> 15:55.453
Oh, I see.
You heard me.

15:55.455 --> 15:57.555
You were just
taken by surprise.

15:57.557 --> 16:00.024
Very well.
Good night.

16:00.026 --> 16:01.559
But--oh!

16:01.561 --> 16:02.994
♪ ♪

16:02.996 --> 16:05.063
[exasperated sigh]

16:05.065 --> 16:07.231
All I wanted to do
was impress captain holt,

16:07.233 --> 16:08.333
And you know what?

16:08.335 --> 16:09.334
It didn't matter.

16:09.336 --> 16:10.668
It didn't matter
that we were late,

16:10.670 --> 16:12.537
It didn't matter
that I was chill,

16:12.539 --> 16:14.439
And it didn't matter
that the rats ate my salad.

16:14.441 --> 16:17.408
I definitely saw them
running away from it.

16:17.410 --> 16:23.147
♪ ♪

16:23.149 --> 16:24.215
You know what,
my friend?

16:24.217 --> 16:26.184
It's time to be chill
for real.

16:26.186 --> 16:29.187
♪ ♪

16:29.189 --> 16:30.188
Mmm.

16:30.190 --> 16:31.622
Yes, gaga! Yes!

16:31.624 --> 16:32.724
That's the spirit!

16:32.726 --> 16:35.193
[both laughing]

16:35.195 --> 16:36.194
We should go.

16:36.196 --> 16:37.261
Yep.

16:37.263 --> 16:39.097
Damn acpd.

16:39.099 --> 16:40.198
They should
be here by now.

16:40.200 --> 16:42.066
(jake)
he's looking at us.

16:42.068 --> 16:43.468
Pretend to use
the ice machine, boyle.

16:43.470 --> 16:44.635
Gladly!

16:44.637 --> 16:46.204
Why is it so fun
to get hotel ice?

16:46.206 --> 16:48.072
It feels wasteful,
but also, like,

16:48.074 --> 16:49.674
"I bought this room.
I deserve this ice."

16:49.676 --> 16:52.343
Shh!
He's on the move.

16:52.345 --> 16:55.346
I'll follow him
till the acpd get here.

16:55.348 --> 16:57.148
[crickets chirping]

16:57.150 --> 16:58.649
Damn it!
Stay put, peralta!

16:58.651 --> 17:00.018
I will!
Don't worry!

17:00.020 --> 17:01.319
I'm just gonna let
sarge follow him.

17:01.321 --> 17:02.520
I'm gonna stay right here.
I can't do it.

17:02.522 --> 17:03.554
I'm gonna cut him off
in the alley!

17:03.556 --> 17:04.555
Ow! Ow! Ow!

17:04.557 --> 17:06.223
[panting]

17:06.226 --> 17:07.625
Ha! Shortcut!

17:07.627 --> 17:09.193
You just got jaked!

17:09.194 --> 17:10.194
[tires screeching]

17:10.195 --> 17:11.194
[jake grunts]

17:11.196 --> 17:13.196
Oh!
Oh, jake!

17:13.199 --> 17:14.598
Oh! Ooh!

17:14.601 --> 17:16.567
Jake! You okay?

17:16.569 --> 17:17.769
No, sarge.

17:17.771 --> 17:20.338
I got hit by a car!

17:20.339 --> 17:22.406
[groans]

17:23.409 --> 17:24.509
Broken ribs
and a million

17:24.511 --> 17:26.077
Broken toes weren't
enough for you?

17:26.079 --> 17:27.712
In retrospect,
they were plenty.

17:27.714 --> 17:30.748
The worst part is,
olson got away.

17:30.750 --> 17:32.283
That's the worst part?

17:32.285 --> 17:34.085
You could've died, man.

17:34.087 --> 17:35.453
I wasn't hurt
that badly.

17:35.455 --> 17:37.488
The doctor said all
my bleeding was internal.

17:37.490 --> 17:39.223
That's where the blood's
supposed to be.

17:39.225 --> 17:40.525
Look,
I know you're angry

17:40.527 --> 17:42.093
Because I disrespected you
as a boss.

17:42.095 --> 17:43.227
No!

17:43.229 --> 17:44.829
I'm upset my friend
doesn't want my help

17:44.831 --> 17:46.597
Because he insists
on being an idiot!

17:46.599 --> 17:47.732
You know what?

17:47.734 --> 17:49.133
You're a lost cause.

17:49.135 --> 17:50.201
I'm done trying
to help you.

17:50.203 --> 17:51.602
Terry's leaving.

17:51.604 --> 17:53.671
Wait.

17:55.275 --> 17:58.810
My second year on the force,
I was working a drug case,

17:58.812 --> 18:01.179
Tracking this
drug dealer for months.

18:01.181 --> 18:02.747
Then, suddenly,
he disappeared

18:02.749 --> 18:04.282
Right before memorial day,

18:04.284 --> 18:05.583
Which I was supposed
to take off

18:05.585 --> 18:07.351
For a guys' weekend
with some friends.

18:07.353 --> 18:09.620
But how?
We didn't know each other yet.

18:09.622 --> 18:12.256
Oh.
Other friends.

18:12.258 --> 18:14.325
While I was gone,
the dude resurfaced

18:14.327 --> 18:16.427
And got into a shootout
with another drug dealer.

18:16.429 --> 18:18.262
Two civilians got shot.

18:18.264 --> 18:21.099
Meanwhile I was sipping
piña coladas in philly.

18:21.101 --> 18:23.301
From that day on, I vowed
to never take time off

18:23.303 --> 18:24.769
During a case.

18:24.771 --> 18:26.704
Also, I don't love philly.

18:26.706 --> 18:27.705
Jake, I get it.

18:27.707 --> 18:28.706
[sighs]

18:28.708 --> 18:29.774
- Philly sucks.
- Yeah.

18:29.776 --> 18:31.175
But why didn't you
ever tell us?

18:31.177 --> 18:32.743
I was embarrassed
about the choice I made.

18:32.745 --> 18:34.512
People got hurt
because of me.

18:34.514 --> 18:36.481
Perps get away.
People get hurt.

18:36.483 --> 18:37.648
That's part of the job.

18:37.650 --> 18:39.484
But if you don't give
yourself a break,

18:39.486 --> 18:41.252
You'll be no use to anyone.

18:41.254 --> 18:43.121
Because you'll be dead.

18:43.123 --> 18:44.122
Real talk alert!

18:44.124 --> 18:45.523
[laughs]

18:45.525 --> 18:46.891
Okay.

18:46.893 --> 18:47.892
I get it.

18:47.894 --> 18:49.127
I'd give you a hug,

18:49.129 --> 18:52.597
The structural integrity
of a chocolate soufflé.

18:52.599 --> 18:54.899
Ooh!

18:54.901 --> 18:57.201
♪ ♪

18:57.203 --> 18:59.370
I am so hungover.

18:59.372 --> 19:02.340
Did we steal these
sunglasses last night?

19:02.342 --> 19:06.477
You paid the bodega guy
$200 for them.

19:06.479 --> 19:07.678
And his shirt.

19:07.680 --> 19:10.248
That explains why
I have a triple xl

19:10.250 --> 19:12.683
<i>Scarface</i> hoodie
on my couch.

19:12.685 --> 19:14.218
Eh, worth it.

19:14.220 --> 19:15.553
It was a pretty
fun night.

19:15.555 --> 19:17.488
Hey, I just wanted
to say I'm sorry

19:17.490 --> 19:19.223
For cancelling
the party so abruptly.

19:19.225 --> 19:22.493
There was a non-emergency
emergency.

19:22.495 --> 19:23.494
(gina)
your loss.

19:23.496 --> 19:24.762
Amy made a salad

19:24.764 --> 19:26.297
And a cake,
and they were...

19:26.299 --> 19:27.298
[smacks lips]

19:27.300 --> 19:28.299
Amazing.

19:28.301 --> 19:29.634
Well, let's put
a make-up dinner

19:29.636 --> 19:32.236
Or we could just
go with the flow.

19:32.238 --> 19:33.404
See what happens.

19:33.406 --> 19:35.239
I don't give a--what?

19:35.241 --> 19:36.240
Too much.

19:36.242 --> 19:37.575
I mean, that
would be great.

19:37.577 --> 19:38.643
Thank you, sir.

19:40.712 --> 19:41.712
Captain.

19:41.714 --> 19:43.581
Detective diaz.

19:44.650 --> 19:45.883
I'm not pregnant.

19:45.885 --> 19:47.251
I see.

19:47.253 --> 19:48.719
I just wanted
to say thank you.

19:49.621 --> 19:51.722
Talking to you
was really helpful.

19:51.724 --> 19:53.724
Maybe mixing our personal
and professional lives

19:53.726 --> 19:55.359
Isn't as disgusting
as it sounds.

19:55.361 --> 19:57.628
Yes, I agree.

19:57.630 --> 20:00.765
And...

20:00.767 --> 20:01.766
I'm glad
I could help.

20:01.768 --> 20:05.603
Now, let's never
talk about...

20:06.638 --> 20:07.638
Stop pointing at it.

20:07.640 --> 20:08.839
Yes. Of course.

20:08.841 --> 20:10.908
Um...

20:10.910 --> 20:11.976
Dismissed?

20:14.513 --> 20:16.214
[sighs]

20:16.216 --> 20:17.448
♪ ♪

20:17.450 --> 20:18.449
Yo!

20:18.451 --> 20:19.517
Welcome back,
peralta.

20:19.519 --> 20:20.551
You look rested.

20:20.553 --> 20:22.920
I caught up on a lot
of very important

20:22.922 --> 20:26.524
I tried grapefruit juice
for the first time--terrible--

20:26.526 --> 20:27.692
And one day,
I even bought

20:27.694 --> 20:28.693
The newspaper.

20:28.695 --> 20:31.495
It was raining, and I
needed a cheap umbrella.

20:31.497 --> 20:32.563
Impressive.

20:32.565 --> 20:34.298
And how's your
broken everything?

20:34.300 --> 20:37.001
To come back to work,
and I'm allowed to have

20:37.003 --> 20:38.569
Light, non-strenuous sex,

20:38.571 --> 20:40.738
Provided I stretch
before and after.

20:40.740 --> 20:41.973
Nice.

20:44.543 --> 20:47.612
Well, it's great
to have you back.

20:48.614 --> 20:50.248
Your perp got picked up
by some uniforms

20:50.250 --> 20:53.751
But I have a couple other
b&es you could jump on.

20:53.753 --> 20:55.319
Oh, actually, sarge,

20:55.321 --> 20:57.521
I'm not back-back
just yet.

20:57.523 --> 20:59.624
I decided to take
two more vacation days.

20:59.626 --> 21:01.425
A friend of mine said
I needed to experience

21:01.427 --> 21:02.426
Life outside of work.

21:02.428 --> 21:03.461
Smart friend.

21:03.463 --> 21:04.795
Anyways, I figured
I owed boyle

21:04.797 --> 21:06.497
A legit trip to ac, so.

21:06.499 --> 21:07.498
That's right, y'all!

21:07.500 --> 21:09.800
It's time for
ac/dc: Part two.

21:09.802 --> 21:12.336
Atlantic city
destruction crew.

21:12.338 --> 21:13.371
Actually, not bad.

21:13.373 --> 21:15.373
Because we are going
to destroy

21:15.375 --> 21:18.342
Eight different
taffy crawls and one

21:18.344 --> 21:21.445
"ghosts of the boardwalk"
bus tour!

21:21.447 --> 21:22.513
Not where
I saw that going,

21:22.515 --> 21:23.547
But I'm still excited!

21:23.549 --> 21:24.548
Ha ho!

21:24.550 --> 21:26.384
This is gonna be epic, bro!

